==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin adjective, ''[[fetidus]]'', “offensive odor” {{italbrac|often incorrectly foetidus, giving rise to the variant spelling}}, originally ''[[fetere]]'', the verb “to stink”.

===Adjective===
'''fœtid''' (also '''[[foetid]]'''), '''more fœtid''', '''most fœtid'''

# Foul-smelling.  See ''[[fetid]]''.

